allIssues.title: Missing Meta Description
allIssues.description: No meta description found. This affects how your page appears in search results.
allIssues.location: <head>
allIssues.suggestion: Add a meta description tag in the `<head>` section of your HTML. This should be a concise summary of the page content, ideally between 150-160 characters. Example: `<meta name="description" content="Your summary here." />`

codeSnippet.after:
<head>
  <title>Page Title</title>
  <meta name="description" content="A compelling description of your page content.">

allIssues.title: Render-Blocking JavaScript in Head
allIssues.description: Found 11 synchronous scripts in <head> that block rendering.
allIssues.location: <head>
allIssues.suggestion: Move the render-blocking JavaScript files to the bottom of the `<body>` section or use the `defer` attribute in the `<script>` tags to ensure they load after the page content. This will improve page load speed and enhance user experience. Example: `<script src="script.js" defer></script>`
